					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I'm not very experienced with VB.NET, but in C# you associate delegate methods to events. Instead of receiving a quit event from a message polling method, a quit event is fired on your application object. Add a delegate method to that event to capture it.<br /><br />See <a href="http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/aa983610(v=vs.71).aspx" class="postlink">Event Handling in Windows Forms (MSDN)</a></div>

