					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The ShowDialog function contains the message loop.  It does all the polling and stuff.<br />Attach event handlers to your form controls to handle them.<br /><br />If you really need to handle the message loop yourself, you can override the function named WndProc within your derived implementation of the Form class.<br /><br />Of course, it's just so much easier to use the forms designer than to try to do everything yourself.<br /><br />VB.NET is basically an inferior version of C#, stay away from it if possible.</div>

					
